&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Verra Mobility is a global leader in smart mobility. We develop technology-driven solutions to make transportation safer and more convenient worldwide. We work with police departments and municipalities across North America, the Asia Pacific and Europe to install safety cameras, including red-light, speed, and school bus stop arm cameras. We manage tolling transactions and violations for the world&#39;s largest commercial fleets and rental car companies, serving over 8.5 million vehicles whilst, via our proprietary connected systems, processing nearly 165 million transactions each year for more than 50 tolling authorities.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verra Mobility is a vibrant and rapidly expanding company that places people at the heart of everything we do. We wholeheartedly embrace our core values:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Do What’s Right, Choose Courage over Comfort, Win Together, &lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Own It&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;in our every interaction with our customers and dedicated team members.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Due to significant growth, and the need to service our valued clients across the region, we are looking for an experienced,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Field Services Technician&lt;/strong&gt;, to be based out of our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Minto&lt;/strong&gt; office and servicing the regional NSW.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will play a pivotal role in installing, maintaining, and monitoring Verra Mobility’s advanced road safety systems, including fixed and mobile speed cameras across the Greater NSW region. This is a highly mobile, hands-on position that combines mechanical precision with technical problem-solving in software and networking, often working at heights and outdoors across diverse environments. As part of our NSW Maintenance Program, you’ll be on the frontline ensuring our life-saving technology operates at peak performance, directly contributing to safer communities across the state&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;permanent, full-time role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is based out of our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Minto office&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and requires working to an established roster across weekdays and occasional weekends, including public holidays and irregular out-of-hours field work. You’ll also support compliance and reporting requirements from the office.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install, commission, and perform preventative and remedial maintenance on road safety technology across metro Sydney and greater NSW.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support a wide range of technical IT solutions, with the ability to resolve complex issues in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installing, configuring, and troubleshooting hardware componentry and software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records, documentation, and reports to meet compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to weekly team initiatives, driving continuous improvement and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply the highest standards of safety in every aspect of your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience installing, configuring, and troubleshooting complex hardware and software systems in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

