&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role is a part of the Verra Command Center team or VCC, which is responsible for remote technical support and oversight of roadside monitoring and enforcement implementations across the United States and parts of Canada. VCC is a 24-hour 7 day a week operation that works to ensure enforcement sites are up, operating, and working for our government clients. We work to provide fast and reliable troubleshooting and monitoring for all devices that fall into our scope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Operations Engineer is a key member of the Verra Command Center (VCC) engineering team, focused on building, integrating, automating, and supporting platforms that ensure the reliability, scalability, and operational stability of roadside operations and supporting IT infrastructure. This role emphasizes system integrations, platform development, infrastructure administration, and advanced scripting to reduce manual effort, improve operational efficiency, and maintain high system availability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Operations Engineer partners closely with Operations Technicians, VCC Technical Leadership, Infrastructure teams, and other Verra Engineering groups to ensure seamless integration between engineering solutions, enterprise IT systems, and day-to-day operations. This position plays a critical role in enabling the VCC to achieve service excellence by developing automation, enhancing monitoring capabilities, troubleshooting complex infrastructure issues, and ensuring roadside products, servers, and supporting platforms operate at peak performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Integration &amp;amp; Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Design, develop, and implement integration solutions across multiple platforms, ensuring data, workflows, and monitoring tools interoperate seamlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automation &amp;amp; Scripting:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and maintain automation tools using Python, PowerShell, C++, other scripting languages and GitHub (revision control) to reduce manual work, improve accuracy, and streamline troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Windows Server &amp;amp; Infrastructure Administration: &lt;/strong&gt;Administer, maintain, and troubleshoot Windows Server environments, including server performance, system services, patching, Active Directory integrations, Group Policy management, and infrastructure reliability. Support virtualization platforms and enterprise infrastructure components as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IT Systems Troubleshooting &amp;amp; Support:&lt;/strong&gt;Perform advanced troubleshooting across servers, applications, databases, networking, storage, and enterprise systems to identify root causes and restore service quickly. Support escalated operational and infrastructure incidents in a 24x7x365 environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration with Operations Teams:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with Operations Technicians and Supervisors to understand frontline needs, translating them into scalable engineering solutions that improve uptime and service quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform Reliability:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and maintain monitoring, alerting, and diagnostic tools that ensure roadside equipment and supporting platforms run at peak efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Engineering:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead and contribute to engineering i

