&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Text&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Verra Mobility is a global technology company supporting safer, smarter and more connected mobility. In Australia, our Government Solutions business delivers technology, software and operational services that support road safety programs.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Project Manager to coordinate the delivery of &lt;strong&gt;software and technology projects&lt;/strong&gt; across company Operations. The role works with software engineering, product, operations, account management and customer stakeholders to manage project plans, delivery tracking, release coordination, risks, dependencies and project communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate assigned software and technology projects from planning through to delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain project plans, status reports, RAID logs, action registers and dashboards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with software engineering, product, operations and customer-facing teams to keep delivery on track.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support release planning, deployment readiness and post-release follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track risks, issues, actions and dependencies, escalating early where required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support customer communication, scope control and project financial tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years’ experience in project coordination or project management, ideally in software, IT or technology delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Agile, Scrum, Kanban or hybrid delivery approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using tools such as Jira, Azure DevOps, Confluence, Microsoft Project, Smartsheet or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the software delivery lifecycle, including requirements, development, testing, release and change control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong stakeholder communication, meeting facilitation, problem-solving and escalation judgement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively with software engineers, testers, product owners, operations teams and customer-facing stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to enterprise software, APIs, databases, cloud platforms or regulated technology environments would be advantageous.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A tertiary qualification in information technology, software engineering, business, project management or a related discipline is preferred.&amp;nbsp;Equivalent practical experience in software or technology project delivery will also be considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management certification such as Agile, Scrum, PRINCE2, PMP or similar would be advantageous, but is not essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply now&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to join a technology-led business delivering software and operational solutions that support road safety outcomes across Australia and the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We value the unique backgrounds, experiences, and contributions that each person brings to our community and encourage and celebrate diversity.&amp;nbsp; First Nations people, those identifying as LGBTQIA+, females, people of all ages, with disabilities and culturally and linguistically diverse people are encouraged to apply. Our aim is to create a workforce that reflects the community in which we live.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&g

