&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Senior Network Engineer reports to the IT Network Engineering Manager and partners closely with Architecture and Operations teams to design, implement, and support enterprise on-premises network infrastructure across LAN, WAN, and data center environments. This role focuses heavily on route/switch engineering, network security, operational stability, and infrastructure modernization initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings strong hands-on expertise in enterprise networking technologies, proven troubleshooting capabilities, and solid project management fundamentals to successfully deliver network initiatives from planning through implementation. This position also serves as a senior technical resource and mentor, helping strengthen team capabilities and operational maturity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and support highly available enterprise LAN, WAN, WLAN, and data center network environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineer and maintain enterprise route/switch infrastructure utilizing technologies such as Aruba, Juniper, HPE, Palo Alto and Fortinet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support firewall and secure connectivity services across core, edge, and remote environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot complex network performance, routing, switching, and connectivity issues while serving as a senior escalation resource&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage infrastructure projects including scope, scheduling, implementation coordination, documentation, and delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional IT teams, business stakeholders, and vendors to support operational and project objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain network diagrams, standards, operational procedures, and technical documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend and implement improvements related to network performance, scalability, resiliency, and security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior engineers and contribute to operational best practices and technical standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support after-hours maintenance windows and occasional travel for infrastructure deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–10 years of experience supporting and engineering enterprise network environments with multiple data centers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on experience with enterprise route/switch technologies and network security platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced understanding of TCP/IP, BGP, OSPF, VLANs, STP, VPNs, and enterprise routing/switching design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting enterprise firewall platforms including Palo Alto, Fortinet, and/or Check Point&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Aruba, Juniper, and HPE networking technologies preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of network monitoring and diagnostic tools such as SolarWinds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Azure and AWS networking concepts is desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven project management fundamentals with experience managing scope, timelines, and implementation activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong troubleshooting, communication, and customer service skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate business requirements into scalable technical solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Industry certifications such as CCNP, PCNSE, NSE, or equivalent are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
